The paper deals with continuous games and proposes a novel algorithm for population dynamics towards Nash equilibrium. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The algorithm is based on the mirror ascent algorithm, which is a popular algorithm in online learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of the augmented Lagrangian method, which is a common optimization technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is decentralized, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a convergence condition, which suggests that it may belong to the Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA) sub-category.
